===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|/prō-krăs'tə-nāt'/}}
http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/call_%27em_as_I_see_%27em

===Etymology===
Borrowed from Latin ''procrastinare'', from ''pro–'' + ''crastinus'' meaning "of or belonging to tomorrow" (from ''crās'' meaning "tomorrow") + English ''–ate''

===Intransitive Verb===
'''procrastinate'''

# to [[put off]]; to [[delay]] doing something; to [[wait]] until [[later]].
#:''He procrastinated until the last minute and had to stay up all night to finish.''

===Transitive Verb===
'''procrastinate'''

# to [[put off]]; to [[delay]] something
#:''"...procrastinate the inevitable."'' - Dick Vitale

